Enthusiastic recruiters engage students, who rehearse their elevator pitches or attend concurrent workshops on networking etiquette in an adjoining classroom. A startup founder invites students to a lunchtime pitch session, and camera crews capture interviews throughout the day. As the event nears its conclusion, announcements signal transitions, prompting students to exit in small groups, carrying tote bags filled with resumes and business materials, while volunteers begin packing up booths and managing leftover brochures.

Workshops on networking etiquette and a panel discussing technical interview preparation occur in an adjoining classroom, where attendance metrics are logged on laptops, and international students queue for advice on visa sponsorship requirements.

Workshops on networking etiquette and an alumni panel on technical interview preparation occur in an adjoining classroom, as volunteers manage brochures and log attendance metrics. Many students exit in small groups carrying tote bags filled with branded notebooks, pens, and business cards, while the atmosphere remains lively, enhanced by the aroma of coffee and catered snacks. Camera crews capture interviews, and a startup founder invites students to a lunchtime pitch session, with discussions on visa sponsorship for international students taking place.
